  "title": "Product Manager (Wastewater Treatment)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Salary & Benefits</strong></p><ul><li><p>Basic: <strong>$5,000 – $7,000</strong> + <strong>Variable Bonus</strong></p></li></ul><p><strong>Working Hours</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Mon – Fri:</strong> 8:00am – 5:00pm</p></li><li><p><strong>Sat:</strong> 8:00am – 12:00pm</p></li></ul><p><strong>Location</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Jurong East</strong></p></li></ul><h2>Responsibilities</h2><ul><li><p>Lead daily operations of hazardous waste treatment lines (evaporation, centrifuges, filtration), ensuring safe operation, quality, and throughput.</p></li><li><p>Optimize operating conditions based on waste characteristics (moisture/oil/salinity/solids) and monitor key parameters (e.g., temperature, pressure, speed, concentration, flux); troubleshoot deviations promptly.</p></li><li><p>Develop and execute production plans based on incoming waste streams and orders; coordinate manpower, equipment availability, and capacity.</p></li><li><p>Manage consumables and critical spares to control cost and minimize downtime.</p></li><li><p>Drive inspections, preventive maintenance, and reliability improvements with the maintenance team; reduce unplanned shutdowns.</p></li><li><p>Maintain strong housekeeping/5S and disciplined site management.</p></li><li><p>Lead production teams (shift planning, training, competency development, performance reviews); ensure compliance with SOPs, EHS, and regulatory requirements; participate in RA/MOC.</p></li><li><p>Support sales/commercial teams with technical feasibility for new waste streams, capacity/timeline inputs, constraints, and cost considerations; provide regular production updates and risk flags.</p></li><li><p>Maintain production documentation and reports; support government/customer/internal audits and inspections.</p></li></ul><h2>Requirements</h2><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s degree (Chemical/Environmental/Process/Mechanical Engineering preferred).</p></li><li>Minimum <strong>10 years</strong> industrial production line experience (hazardous waste/ chemical/ environmental/ resource recovery preferred) with proven plant/operations management experience.</li><li>Hands-on experience in <strong>evaporation (multi-effect/MVR)</strong>, <strong>industrial centrifuges (decanter/disc-stack)</strong>, and/or <strong>solid-liquid separation/filtration</strong> (filter press/bag/candle).</li></ul><p><p><em>Only shortlisted candidates would be notified</em></p><p>MTC Consulting Pte Ltd | 15C7752<br />EA. Registration No.: R22111807 | Yap Teng Hui</p></p>",
